        Properties 
        Name Description
        TravelSector
        Identifies the travel sector. Refer to OpenTravel Code List Travel Sector (TVS).
        Details
        Type TravelSector_Enum
        Example Value Air
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        Privacy
        Permission for sharing data for synchronization of information held by other travel service providers.
        Details
        Type Privacy
        Example Value ???
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        VendorCode
        Indicate the partner(s)/vendor(s) for which the customer loyalty number is valid.
        Details
        Type Code
        Example Value Example String Value
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1

        Max Occurrences 1

        Details

        Example Value 2342
        Required false
        Pattern N/A

        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        allianceLoyaltyLevelName

        Example Value Emerald
        Required false

        Max Occurrences 1

        Required false

      • Indicator Summary

        Indicators 
        Name Description
        expireDateExclusiveIndicatorInd
        When true, indicates that the ExpireDate is the first day after the applicable period (e.g. when expire date is Oct 15 the last date of the period is Oct 14).
        primaryLoyaltyIndicatorInd
        When true, indicates this is the primary customer loyalty program and when false, indicates this is not the primary customer loyalty program.
